                    "comment": "wesm commented on issue #3094: ARROW-3326: [Python] Add NativeFile.align method, wrapping arrow::ipc::AlignStream\nURL: https://github.com/apache/arrow/pull/3094#issuecomment-444509407\n \n \n   Well, this is available in Ruby already, so this is partly for API parity\r\n   \r\n   https://github.com/apache/arrow/blob/9d007b1eed283af6cf3b2120f36bced1b27cfe73/c_glib/test/test-buffer-input-stream.rb#L34\r\n   \r\n   This patch doesn't have much to do with IPC directly. Alignment issues are part of the IPC protocol implementation -- if we want to change anything there we should examine in a separate JIRA.\r\n   \r\n   I've adopted the long-term view that these classes may be used for many purposes -- if the user is producing a serialized message of some kind from the Python API without necessarily using the built-in IPC protocol classes, it would be useful to be able to write alignment bytes without having to resort to arithmetic by hand.\n\n----------------------------------------------------------------\nThis is an automated message from the Apache Git Service.\nTo respond to the message, please log on GitHub and use the\nURL above to go to the specific comment.\n \nFor queries about this service, please contact Infrastructure at:\nusers@infra.apache.org\n",
